<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 03 at 1:14AM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Cherokee and Clay Counties through 200 AM EDT...
At 114 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hayesville, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Andrews, Hayesville, Nantahala Lake, Shooting Creek, Tusquitee,
Topton, Brasstown and Marble.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
